React 2nd class


1. Difference between ECMAScript (ES) and JavaScript (JS)
ECMAScript (ES)

ECMAScript is a standard

It defines rules, syntax, and features for scripting languages

It does not run by itself

Examples:

ES5, ES6 (2015), ES7, ES8…

JavaScript (JS)

JavaScript is a programming language

It follows ECMAScript rules

It can run in browsers and servers (Node.js)

Used to build web applications

Difference Table
ECMAScript (ES)	JavaScript (JS)
Specification / Standard	Programming Language
Defines syntax & rules	Implements ES rules
Cannot run alone	Runs in browser / server
Updated as ES versions	Uses ES features

Example:
ES6 introduced let, const, arrow functions → JavaScript uses them.

2. Parent Tag Rule in React (JSX)

Inside the return() of a React component:

Only one parent element is allowed

All HTML must be wrapped in a single parent tag

Correct Examples
return (
  <div>
    <h1>Hello</h1>
    <p>Welcome</p>
  </div>
);


OR using Fragment

return (
  <>
    <h1>Hello</h1>
    <p>Welcome</p>
  </>
);

Why this rule?

JSX converts code into JavaScript objects

JavaScript can return only one object

3. Component Naming Rule in React

Component name must start with a capital letter

If written in small letters, React treats it as an HTML tag

Correct
import Home from "./Home";
<Home />

Incorrect
<home />   // React thinks this is an HTML tag

4. Self-Closing Tags in React

Tags without content must be self-closing

Examples
<img />
<input />
<br />
<hr />
<Home />


❌ <img>
✔ <img />

5. Importing and Calling Components in App.jsx
Importing a Component
import Home from "./Home";

Calling a Component
function App() {
  return (
    <>
      <Home />
    </>
  );
}

export default App;

Why App.jsx?

App.jsx is the main container

All components are rendered inside App.jsx

6. Importance of index.html

It is the root HTML file

React app loads inside this file

Contains a <div id="root"></div>

Browser first loads index.html

<div id="root"></div>


React injects UI inside this div

Mostly unchanged (except for SEO)

7. Importance of main.jsx

main.jsx is the starting point of React

It connects:

index.html

App.jsx

Role of main.jsx

Renders the React application

Uses ReactDOM.createRoot

Wraps App inside StrictMode

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root")).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <App />
  </React.StrictMode>
);

8. Flow of Execution in React
Browser
   ↓
index.html
   ↓
main.jsx
   ↓
App.jsx
   ↓
Components
 
ES6 features
Arrow function 
variables-- let and const
destructuring -extract from object


 
